Gulf of Grief07279obn3lqbsogrsojiy2602l772b9wyvmg1786202015-03-22T19:22:55ZThe Dragon Demands5014364/* References */{{Quote|Nobody remembers if the waters around Ghis had names before the empire. But ever since we know them only as Slaver's Bay... and the Gulf of Grief.|Ser [[Jorah Mormont]]|Old Ghis &amp; Slaver's Bay (Histories &amp; Lore)}}
[[Image:Gulf of Grief.png|thumb|right|200px|A map showing the location of the Gulf of Grief along the southern coast of Essos.]]
[[Image:Slaver's Bay Title Sequence.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The Gulf of Grief and Slaver's Bay as depicted in the title sequence.]]
'''The Gulf of Grief''' is a body of water located south of [[Slaver's Bay]]. It is an inlet of the [[Summer Sea]] and separates the shattered lands of [[Valyria]] from the region of [[Ghiscar]]. Slaver's Bay itself is a large bay on the northern side of the Gulf of Grief.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/locations/valyria/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 map, Valyria entry]&lt;/ref&gt;
